<html>
<head>
    <title>HTML Lists Example</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
        }
        h2 {
            color: #2e6da4;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <h1>HTML Lists Demonstration</h1>

    <h2>1. Ordered List</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Wake up</li>
        <li>Brush your teeth</li>
        <li>Have breakfast</li>
        <li>Go to work</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>2. Unordered List</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Apples</li>
        <li>Bananas</li>
        <li>Cherries</li>
        <li>Grapes</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Nested Lists</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Fruits
            <ul>
                <li>Apple</li>
                <li>Mango</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Vegetables
            <ul>
                <li>Carrot</li>
                <li>Spinach</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Ordered List inside an Unordered List</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Steps to Prepare Tea:
            <ol>
                <li>Boil water</li>
                <li>Add tea leaves</li>
                <li>Add milk and sugar</li>
                <li>Strain and serve</li>
            </ol>
        </li>
        <li>Enjoy your tea!</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Definition List</h2>
    <dl>
        <dt>HTML</dt>
        <dd>HyperText Markup Language - the standard language for creating web pages.</dd>
        <dt>CSS</dt>
        <dd>Cascading Style Sheets - used to style HTML elements.</dd>
        <dt>JavaScript</dt>
        <dd>A scripting language used to create dynamic content on web pages.</dd>
    </dl>

</body>
</html>
